gomodel:SYNGO_4528  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 5: L1CAM expression in PyNs is required not only for the formation but also for the maintenance of axo-axonal synapses as shown by the induction of L1CAM knockdown at postnatal day 28 and analysis at day P40 (panels L-O).\nIn addition, Fig. 6 shows that localization of L1CAM depends on the presence of Ankyrin G. (see also related annotation #4526 for synapse assembly)\n\n26/02/2021 Dnyanada: The average number of gephyrin puncta per GFP puncta in the axon initial segment of the pyramidal neuron was decreased in L1CAM knockdown compared to control.. Experimental description: Temporal expression profile of endogenous L1CAM at the AIS of PyNs in LII of somatosensory cortex from CD1 mice (Legend to Fig. 5/p.366)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2021-02-26" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4528" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

